<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Lunge">Dumbbell Lunge</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-lunge" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell lunge</a> is a frequently utilized exercise for both novice and advanced alike. Known for being a unilateral movement, dumbbell lunges are excellent for functional movement. Think of going up and down stairs, getting off the floor, and even walking.&nbsp;</p>



<p>All of these movements require the mobility and strength that lunges provide!</p>



<p>Dumbbell lunges target the quadriceps, glutes, hamstrings, and adductors. Muscles within the core also help keep you upright during the movement. As you build strength in the lunge, you’ll also decrease injury risk, improve posture, and improve <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6006536/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">sports performance</a>.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="03361201-Dumbbell-Lunge_Hips-FIX2_" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/967445061?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Dumbbell Lunge Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Begin in a standing position with your feet hip-distance apart. Grasp two dumbbells by the handles, and turn your palms facing your thighs. Keep your chest high and your shoulder blades retracted.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Take a large step forward with your right foot, keeping your torso upright. Your weight should be through the ball of your left foot and the entire right foot. Your hips should be neutral and forward.&nbsp;</li>



<li>With shoulder blades down and back, inhale and engage your core. Bend both knees, bringing the left knee down toward the floor. Your right thigh should be parallel to the floor.</li>



<li>Pause just above the ground. Exhale, squeeze your glutes and press firmly through your right foot to bring yourself back to the starting position. Your feet should now be hip-distance apart.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Repeat as desired.&nbsp;</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul>
<li>Ensure that your knees stay directly over your ankle bones.&nbsp;</li>



<li>Stay in control of the movement. Avoid hitting your knee on the ground.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



<div class="wp-block-group medicine-table is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container">
